-- White House would consider tax break on foreign profits
-- 
-- Mon Mar 7, 2011 1:35pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/03/07/us-usa-taxes-repatriation-idUSTRE7264XY20110307

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The White House said on Monday it would consider, as part of an overhaul of the tax code, a tax break for companies on foreign profits brought back to the United States. 

 White House spokesman Jay Carney told a briefing a so-called repatriation holiday was something the Obama administration would consider as part of tax reform. (Reporting by  Jeff Mason , Editing by Sandra Maler)